items.name: Linux Wiki
items.title: Linux Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Linux wiki!
items.desc:
Welcome to the Linux wiki, an online resource about the Linux OS family that anyone can edit! Linux is a computer operating system family, as well as one of the most prominent examples of free software and open source development; its underlying source code can be modified, used, and redistributed by anyone, freely.

Predominantly known for its use in servers, Linux receives use as an operating system for a wider variety of computer hardware than any other operating system, including desktop computers, supercomputers, mainframes, and embedded devices such as cellphones. Linux is packaged for different uses in Linux distributions.

items.name: Last Exile
items.title: Last Exile
items.headline: Take to the skies at the Last Exile Wikia
items.desc: Last Exile (ラストエグザイル, Rasuto Eguzairu) is a Japanese animated television series created by Gonzo. It featured a production team led by director Koichi Chigira, character designer Range Murata, and production designer Mahiro Maeda. The three had previously worked together in Blue Submarine No. 6, one of the first CG anime series. Last Exile premiered on TV Tokyo on April 7, 2003 and ran for twenty-six episodes until its conclusion on September 29, 2003.

items.name: X-Files Wiki
items.title: X-Files Wiki
items.headline: The X-Files Wiki
items.desc: The X-Files Wiki is a community database that gives all the details, information, data, and facts about The X-Files universe with episode summaries, character biographies, conspiracies, weapons, artifacts, and of course, aliens and paranormal activities. This wiki also gives information from the television series Millennium and The Lone Gunmen. Read about the mysteries of paranormal activities and follow the X-Files unit as they uncover The Truth.

items.name: KanzakaDex
items.title: KanzakaDex
items.headline: Welcome to KanzakaDex
items.desc:
The ultimate Slayers, Lost Universe, and Hajime Kanzaka resource.

Hajime Kanzaka (Japanese: 神坂一) is a Japanese fiction author who created Slayers, Lost Universe, and a myriad of other series. 

Before becoming a professional novelist, Kanzaka worked in an office. In the late 1980s he noticed that Dragon Magazine was holding an amateur fiction contest. His entry won first prize in the contest. The story was soon to be serialized in the magazine for over a decade, with its side series, Slayers Special, serialized in the magazine to this day.

items.desc: The Star Trek galaxy just got a whole log bigger. Here at Star Trek Expanded Universe, we strive to document everything there is to know about Role-Playing Games, fan fiction, and fan films. We also allow fanon! If you're a Trekker who knows something about any of these subjects, feel free to share your knowledge and passion. After all, this is a site anyone can edit, including you!

items.name: Half-Life Wiki
items.title: Half-Life Wiki

items.desc: Half-Life Wiki is a comprehensive encyclopedia focusing on the Half-Life and Portal universe by collecting information such as the games, characters, enemies, creatures, factions, locations, weapons, technology, and more.

items.name: Legendary Journeys
items.title: Legendary Journeys
items.headline: Legendary Journeys Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the Legendary Journeys Wiki, the collaborative Hercules & Xena database that anyone can edit. This site uses a POV from within the various television series, and therefore treats characters, like Hercules and Xena, as real beings, and also gods, such as Zeus or Bacchus, as beings that truly existed. The most important part of this website is that anyone, even you, can edit just about anything! Enter now to learn more!

items.name: Star Wars: Exodus Visual Encyclopedia
items.title: Star Wars: Exodus Visual Encyclopedia
items.headline: Welcome to the Star Wars: Exodus Visual Encyclopedia
items.desc:
Star Wars: Exodus is a roleplaying community that has been around since Feburary 14, 2003. However, before we formed Star Wars: Exodus we were on the Sony Star Wars Galaxies Roleplaying Forum, since roughly the year 1999 or 2000. The purpose of this site is to help members new and old remember, or get to know, the stories of the past. Furthermore, new stories are added as they are developed.

In all of the reading material that can be found at the Exodus boards, it is easy to get lost with the masses of information presented. So, as well as serving as a grounds for recording past and present stories, the Visual Encyclopedia also allows for the implementation of other story-enhancing features. Whether they be a personal character, or an entire galaxy-wide government, it is all here, in the Visual Encyclopedia.

items.name: Matrix Wiki
items.title: Matrix Wiki
items.headline: What If I Told You...You have Found The MetaCortex Database!
items.desc: This wiki is dedicated to the Matrix film trilogy and related short stories. As a narrative, the Matrix saga tells of a war between a human resistance and a race of sentient Machines, who imprison humanity within a virtual reality known as the Matrix. The Matrix films center on The One, a man with a special ability and an important destiny. Woven throughout the main story of The Matrix are various threads of background stories that cut across different mediums, including the main trilogy as well as comics, video games and the Animatrix animated series. Beyond the surface story the Matrix is rich in explorations and allusions to various questions in philosophy, theology, psychology, sociology, politics and computer science.

Joined by her team of unforgettable judges, Tyra has taken a hold of the reality world with her show.

items.desc: Kyle XY was an American television series produced by ABC Family about a boy who wakes up in the forest outside of Seattle with no memory. The story follows Kyle as he tries to discover who he is and why he has no memory before that day. We meet the family that takes him in, the kids' friends and where they go to school and work. The premise is science fiction, but the setting was present-day at the time of the productions (2006-2009).

items.name: Annex

Basically, any fiction-related articles threatened with deletion at Wikipedia may be posted here. Reasonable non-fiction articles threatened with deletion may be posted as well.

items.name: Mass Effect Wiki
items.title: Mass Effect Wiki

items.desc: Mass Effect is a game series developed by Bioware. The inital release was in January 2007 with several sequels published since then. It is a Sci-Fi RPG. Most stories focus on one of the minor players in this War: Faction Paradox, a shadowy time-travelling cult that relishes creating chaos in the timeline. The Faction first appeared in the Doctor Who novels, but you don't have to be a Doctor Who fan to enjoy Faction Paradox: all you need is a love of experimental stories and crazy ideas!

items.name: Alex Rider Wiki

items.name: LaTeX Wiki
items.title: LaTeX Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the LaTeX wiki!
items.desc:
Welcome to LaTeX Wiki, the wiki about LaTeX that anyone can edit!

LaTeX (formatted as LATEX, pronounced /ˈlɑːtɛx/, /ˈlɑːtɛk/, /ˈleɪtɛx/, or /ˈleɪtɛk/), is a document markup language and document preparation system for the TeX typesetting program. The term LaTeX refers only to the language in which documents are written, not to the editor application used to write those documents. In order to create a document in LaTeX, a .tex file must be created using some form of text editor. While most text editors can be used to create a LaTeX document, a number of editors have been created specifically for working with LaTeX.

Created and maintained by the Dead Space community, with over a thousand articles available, it serves as the definitive source for anything  Dead Space; covering the games, books, films, comics, as well as characters, Necromoprhs, weapons, chapters, and much more. 
So, come say hi!

The story focuses on a young boy named Gon Freecss who departs on a journey to find his father, a world-renowned Hunter. Along the way, Gon meets his friends: Kurapika, the last remaining member of the Kurta clan; Leorio, a physician who desires the financial benefits that Hunters receive; and Killua Zoldyck, a boy who left his former life as a member of the world's most daengrous family of assassins.

items.headline: Hunter x Hunter Database
items.desc:
Bienvenue dans Hunter x Hunter Database! 
Nous sommes heureux de votre visite sur ce wiki complet consacré au manga de Yoshihiro Togashi!
Ce wiki traite du célèbre Shōnen: Hunter x Hunter, tout le wiki est à votre disposition ainsi que les administrateurs.
N'hésitez pas à venir contribuer ou encore débattre via les forums et le tchat.
Bonne visite sur le wiki!
